f polemical fiction later in her career. In the unfinished draft of her "essay-nove;" The Pargiters, Woolf created a brilliant new narrative form allowing her to make unequivocal value judgments.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAmbiguity in literature. 0aEnglish fictionxWomen authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aModernism (Literature). 4aEurope. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aWomens Studies.  aVirginia Woolf, Elizabeth Robins, feminist novelists, Woolf's feminism, modern literacy, gender and identity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501714474?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501714474423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501714474/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles